}
<style>
	.wo-forumcontent p {
		text-align: justify;
	}
</style>
@if (!RTL) //English
{
	<!-- PAGE CONTAINER START -->
	<div class="page-container">
		<!-- MAIN START -->
		<section class="wo-main-section wo-main-section-50">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="row justify-content-md-center">
					<div class="col-12">
						<div class="wo-sectionhead">
							<div class="wo-sectionhead__title">
								@*<span>Great Review From Owners</span>*@
								<h2>@Html.Raw(Resources.REFUND_POLICY_TAG)</h2>
							</div>
							@*<div class="wo-sectionhead__description">
									<p>Consectetur adipisicing elit sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore etdolore magna aliqua enim adinim ullamco laborisn nisi ut aliquip exea commodo eniam quis nostrud exercitation consequat</p>
								</div>*@
						</div>
						<div class="wo-forumsingle-section wo-forumsingle-section-50">
							<div class="wo-forumcontent">
								<div class="wo-forumcontent__title">
									<h3>The policy for Refunds </h3>
								</div>
								<div class="wo-forumcontent__title">
									<h3>Deposit, Cancellation and Refund Policy</h3>
								</div>
								<div class="wo-forumcontent__description">
									<p>
										The policy of nowbuysell.com for deposits, the process of Refunds and cancellations varies person to person and supplier to supplier and it also depends on the type of a vehicle. The policy will be detailed on the quote and confirmation email you receive and we recommend that you check with the branch you are hiring from if you have any queries.
									</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							<div class="wo-forumcontent">
								<div class="wo-forumcontent__title">
									<h3>Here is a general guide:</h3>
								</div>
								<div class="wo-forumcontent__description">
									<p>
										1. After the booking is done, as per Terms and Conditions of nowbuysell.com and also on the basis of Rental Agreement. Here are some more terms and conditions which need to be followed properly:
									</p>
									<p>
										(a) If some accident occurred then nowbuysell.com and the supplier are not responsible for it and it's not their duty to supply another vehicle. The supplier is not responsible to refund the hired term. It is totally up to the supplier if he wants to supply any other vehicle for you. If it is not the driver’s fault in the accident then nowbuysell.com can help you sort the problem out.
									</p>
									<p>
										(b) In such a case in which the rentee end its ride on the vehicle before the given time then he would not be refunded for the remaining hired time.
									</p>
									<p>
										2. Some but not all locations require a minimum 10% deposit of the total hire value might inclusive of GST. This may be taken at the time of booking although not all locations require this. A 20% non-refundable deposit is required at time of booking for specialist vehicles (add some special vehicles here), again not every location requires this, please check with the location chosen.
									</p>
									<p>
										In the event that you cancel your reservation, a cancellation fee may apply as follows (however this policy does vary supplier by supplier and by vehicle type):
									</p>
									<p>
										(a) If you cancel your booking after 7 days of rent, 10% cancellation fee would be charged. 10% refund would not be given and if someone's deposit was not charged then a fee equal to 10% of the hire value will be payable.
									</p>
									<p>
										(b) If you cancel your booking before seven days then full amount will be refunded. FULL REFUND/NO CANCELLATION FEE.
									</p>
									<p>
										(c) A supplier may give a full or half refund to discreted users. The refund policy is not for the no show customers.
									</p>
									<p>
										3. The cancellation process should be sent in written to the website and the supplier (via emails). When the hire is cancelled a confim cancellation email will be sent to you so that you know about your hire. May be any charges are deducted as per policy.
									</p>
									<p>
										4. If a "No-Show" has confirmed a booking through website or through telephone and then he cancels the ride then no Refunds would be granted.
									</p>
									<p>
										5. Bookings of a van and coaster:
									</p>
									<p>
										10-20% of the total deposit will be taken from the total hire value (might include tax) WILL be taken on the coaster and van bookings.
									</p>
									<p>
										You will receive no refund if you do not pick up the car, regardless of which rental supplier you use. What rental companies call a ‘no show’ does not only mean that you did not show up. It also applies if you are not able to take the car for other reasons.
									</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							<div class="wo-forumcontent">
								<div class="wo-forumcontent__title">
									<h3>Damage refunds</h3>
								</div>
								<div class="wo-forumcontent__description">
									<p>
										Not a single penny would be refunded if the damage to the vehicle is caused by the violation of the traffic rules or violation of the lease agreement, or if the opposite party refuse to be guilty for such a damage.
									</p>
									<p>
										If a vehicle got any kind of damage, then the amount will be deducted from the drivers’ credit card or debit card. The damage to the interior of the car, glass, tires, it's gearbox, underbody, roof of the vehicle, clutch, engine oil pan, the damage due to the third-class fuel, damage resulting from certain accidents.
									</p>
									<p>
										The refund does not cover any damage or loss of personal belongings, theft of a car in case of loss of keys, lost profits of the rental supplier as a result of the inability to use the car, costs of technical assistance on the road, costs of towing the car, any handling fees in the event of damage to the vehicle (if applicable), administration fees, and any subsequent personal expenses such as telephone bills, hotel accommodations, public transportation, taxis. A refund is also not possible if the accident occurred due to a violation of local traffic rules and / or if the driver received a fine and / or if the insurance company (even in the case of a third party involved) refused to return the money. All rental agreements are subject to the laws of UAE.
									</p>
									<p>
										Deductible refunds do not include: damage to the interior and gearbox.
									</p>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
		<!-- MAIN END -->
	</div>
	<!-- PAGE CONTAINER END -->
}
